### Training data — `fetch.py → ERA5 Historical API`

| Variable | Source | Tag |
|----------|--------|-----|
| `temperature_2m` | 🟢 Open-Meteo ERA5 archive API | **LIVE** |
| `wind_speed_10m` | 🟢 Open-Meteo ERA5 archive API | **LIVE** |
| `wind_direction_10m` | 🟢 Open-Meteo ERA5 archive API | **LIVE** |
| `precipitation` | 🟢 Open-Meteo ERA5 archive API | **LIVE** |
| `boundary_layer_height` | 🟢 Open-Meteo ERA5 archive API | **LIVE** |
| `temperature_850hPa` | 🟢  Open-Meteo ERA5 (pressure level) | **LIVE** (falls back to `NaN` if unavailable) |

> **Verdict: All weather training data is genuinely real.** No fakes.

