## 6. Green Buffers

| Component | Source | Tag | Detail |
|-----------|--------|-----|--------|
| **OSM land use query** | 🟢 Overpass API | **LIVE** (when it works) | Queries for industrial/farmland/scrub/grass/orchard/forest polygons |
| **OSM timeout fallback** | 🟠 Hardcoded lat/lon offsets | **HARDCODED FALLBACK** | If Overpass times out (which it does ~80% of the time from Tunisia), the code uses 15-20 manually written coordinate offsets per city |
| **Buffer scores** | 🟡 Computed from algorithm | **FORMULAIC** | Uses upwind position, land type, proximity, coastal proximity — but the weights are hand-tuned |
| **Location names** | 🟠 Proximity lookup to landmark table | **HARDCODED** | 7 named landmarks per city, manually chosen |
| **Species recommendations** | 🔴 Hardcoded | **FULLY SYNTHETIC** | `Pinus halepensis`, `Eucalyptus globulus`, etc. — from Mediterranean reforestation literature but not site-specific |
| **NO₂ reduction percentages** | 🔴 Literature estimates | **FULLY SYNTHETIC** | "25–40%" for industrial perimeters — from published studies, not measured on-site |
| **Area needed** | 🔴 Hardcoded | **FULLY SYNTHETIC** | `5000 m²` for industrial, `2000 m²` for others — arbitrary numbers |

> **Current state: Both cities are using the hardcoded fallback** because the Overpass API timed out during the last regeneration.

